      • getPermutation

        protected int[] getPermutation()
        Description copied from class: ListChangeListener.Change
        If this change is an permutation, it returns an integer array that describes the permutation. This array maps directly from the previous indexes to the new ones. This method is not publicly accessible and therefore can return an array safely. The method is used by ListChangeListener.Change.wasPermutated() and ListChangeListener.Change.getPermutation(int) methods.
